summary: An Ordinance accepting deeds from F. W. Keen and Christena Keen, his wife, E. K. Worthington and Mabel L. Worthington, his wife, executed on August 1, 1922, and the Drew Investment Company, a corporation, executed on the 8th day of November, 1922, conveying certain property to The City of Seattle for park purposes; providing for the execution of certain mortgages in payment for said property, and declaring an emergency.
